    "ideation": "The videocassette animation personifies the mechanical soul of analog media: a cycle of loading, tracking, playing, and the occasional glitch. The eyes represent the two tape reels, spinning in sync or fluttering when the 'tracking' goes out. The mouth acts as the scanline on a cathode ray tube, starting as a static-filled hiss before resolving into a smooth, rolling waveform as the movie plays. The color palette uses a nostalgic 'night mode' aesthetic with tracking-error magentas, static cyans, and phosphor-burn greens. The final beat is a sudden 'eject' where the eyes snap wide and the color drains, signaling the end of the tape.",
